Cloud-based security is centralized and costs less. You dno't have any hardware and everything is handled by third-party.
You have no physical access to the data center. Third-party may have access to your data. Security and sygnatures updates are automated. Scalable security options, 
it is not as customizable as in your own data center but it is faster.  

On-promises puts the security burden on the client. You have data center and infrastructure that may costs a lot. You have full controll about evry aspect of security. 
Adding additional security may couze problems.


